
[[Image:Googlematrixwikipedia2009.jpg|thumb|240px|  Fig.1. Google matrix of Wikipedia articles network, written in the bases of PageRank index; fragment of
top  200 X 200  matrix elements is shown, total size
N=3282257 (from 19)]]
A Google matrix is a particular stochastic matrix that is used by Google's PageRank algorithm. The matrix represents a graph with edges representing links between pages.
The rank of each page can be generated iteratively from the Google matrix using the power method. However, in order for the power method to converge, the matrix must be stochastic, irreducible and aperiodic.

==H matrix==

In order to generate the Google matrix, we must first generate a matrix H representing the relations between pages or nodes.
Assuming there are n pages, we can fill out H by doing the following:

